ay a pivotal role in shaping the future of defense organizations and their partners by guiding them in their use of emerging technologies and data to drive operational resilience, enable seamless multi-domain integration and interoperability and strengthen workforce readiness as they navigate the complexities of today’s geopolitical landscape.<br><br>What You Will Do<br><br><ul><li>Track European and global defense market trends, relevant vendors, emerging technologies, and best practices to advise CIOs and IT Executives in staying ahead in a constantly evolving technology landscape and changing geopolitical uncertainties</li><li>Build credibility as a defense technology and data expert for CIOs and IT Executives expert representing Gartner Business and Technology Insights</li><li>Actively participate in ideation and research community discussions to establish strong positions on topics that impact Government CIOs and develop research</li><li>Lead qualitative and quantitative studies to establish thought-provoking insights for our C-level clients</li><li>Write evidence-based content that is easily consumed, defensible and actionable. </li><li>Deliver high-quality, actionable advice to an executive client audience (e.g., CIOs, program executive officers, CTOs, etc.) through a variety of media. </li><li>Create and deliver thought-provoking presentations for webinars, executive briefings and other client-facing events. </li><li>Deliver outstanding sales and service support to retain and grow the Gartner business.. </li><li>Identify research process improvements or develop new processes that help the team and the Business and Technology Insights group excel in delivering client value</li><li>Be a mentor and a coach by supporting more junior team members<br><br></li></ul>What You’ll Need<br><br><ul><li>12+ years of relevant IT and/or program executive leadership working for an EMEA or NATO defense organization and with its ecosystem of allies, partners, IT vendors and contractors</li><li>Bachelor's degree or equivalent experience; Graduate degree preferred</li><li>An informed understanding of the strategic and operational challenges facing defense leaders within and across military domains (i.e., land, sea, air, space, cyber)</li><li>Extensive experience in European defense leading strategy and/or implementation of programs and technical capabilities in one or more of the following areas:</li><li>AI strategy, solutions and/or implementation, including data readiness</li><li>Data integration and visualization for the purpose of establishing a common operating picture in defense</li><li>Cybersecurity and resilience trends and program requirements</li><li>IT infrastructure and operations, including cloud services and edge computing</li><li>Quantum computing trends</li><li>Autonomous systems</li><li>Multi-domain command and control systems</li><li>Communication and information systems</li><li>Demonstrate executive presence; can immediately establish credibility with executives and additional stakeholders</li><li>Learning agility and adeptness with navigating highly matrixed environments</li><li>Ability to work in a highly collaborative environment. </li><li>Strong organizational skills: with the ability to work under tight deadlines and produce high-quality deliverables</li><li>Strong communicator who can explain complex concepts concisely and simply. </li><li>Strong written and verbal proficiency, analytical and presentation skills; ability to engage clients and respond effectively to questions. </li><li>Proficient in analyzing and synthesizing data; can effectively apply patterns and frameworks while drawing and defending conclusions to client challenges. </li><li>Ability to work independently, while also being intrinsically motivated to collaborate across teams and support the workflow of others, in a multicultural global team<br><br></li></ul>Preferred Education and Experience:<br><br><ul><li>Master's degree or equivalent degree pr