iance with regulatory guidelines (ICH, EMA, FDA) and internal quality standards.o Serve as a senior reviewer and quality gatekeeper for key deliverables.• Strategic &amp; Customer-Facing Responsibilitieso Function as a senior point of contact for customers, providing strategic guidance on regulatory writing projects.o Support business development activities, including proposal development and presentations.o Contribute to the external facing side of Azur Health Science by deepening your knowledge on rare diseases, writing articles or white papers for publication, and participating in team events to engage with the rare disease community.Qualifications &amp; Experience• Experience:o Minimum 10 years of experience in regulatory medical writing, actively writing documents.o At least 5 years of interacting directly with customers, coordinating study teams and leading meetings relating to medical writing deliverables, ideally in an agency environment.o At least 3 years of experience in line management or leadership roles within a medical writing team.o Actively worked on ≥ 4 FDA or EMA submissions for marketing authorisation, ≥ 10 protocols, ≥ 10 CSRs, and ≥ 10 investigator’s brochures, briefing document, orphan drug designation/maintenance report or other scientific advice document, or response to agency questions.o An ability to manage several parallel projects under demanding timelines.o At ease with and experience of working with multiple accounts and document management systems and software.o Demonstrated expertise in rare diseases and/or orphan drug development.o In-depth knowledge of global regulatory requirements and submission processes.• Qualifications:o Ideally, a higher level degree (Bachelor's/Masters) in a science or language discipline.o An eye for detail yet an understanding of the balance between high quality and perfection.o Impeccable written and spoken English.o Understanding of and adaptability to different personalities and cultures.o Ability to accept different learning styles, including learning through mistakes.o At ease with communicating internally and with multiple-stakeholder customer teams.Why Join Azur?A rare opportunity to lead a highly skilled team in a dynamic, customer-focused environment.Work on impactful projects in rare disease and cutting-edge therapies.Conditions• Location: Mulhouse, France or Germany home or hybrid working• On-site presence: required twice weekly during the initial onboarding month, followed by a minimum of four in-person meetings per year• Contract: Full-time, CDI, cadre – forfait jours (FR), full-time permanent 40h/week (DE)• Start Date: Flexible, ideally November 2025 but open until January 2026• Salary: Starting gross annual salary at €60,000• Competitive compensation and benefits package.If you are interested in this position, please email your tailored CV and covering letter to recruitment@azurhealthscience.com.For more information on how we handle your personal data during the recruitment process, please refer to our Recuitment Privacy Policy: https://azurhealthscience.com/recruitment-privacy-policy/.",
