  "descriptionHtml": "<p><strong>WHO ARE WE?</strong></p><p>TMC is an international high-tech consulting company that provides its expertise to help clients overcome their challenges. For <strong>25 years</strong>, with a global presence in <strong>16 countries</strong>, we have built a reputation for excellence and reliability through <strong>Employeneurship</strong> in various fields: <strong>Technology &amp; Engineering, Energy &amp; Renewables, Life Sciences &amp; Pharm, Digital &amp; IT.</strong></p><p><br></p><p><strong>| YOUR CHALLENGE ?</strong></p><p>We are seeking a <strong>Digital Physical Implementation Expert</strong> to join our Digital Competence Center, working in a <strong>mixed-signal environment</strong> with a strong focus on <strong>automotive-grade semiconductor products</strong>. In this role, you will lead the <strong>full physical design flow from RTL to GDSII</strong>, ensuring high-performance, power-efficient, and reliable designs that meet strict automotive standards.</p><p>Your expertise in <strong>Static Timing Analysis (STA)</strong>, <strong>floorplanning</strong>, and <strong>physical implementation optimization</strong> will be instrumental in driving the success of our next-generation mixed-signal ICs.</p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>Physical Design Ownership</strong>: Lead the implementation of digital blocks from RTL to GDSII, achieving optimal <strong>PPA (Power, Performance, Area)</strong> while ensuring compliance with automotive quality and reliability standards.</li><li><strong>Floorplanning &amp; Power Planning</strong>: Develop advanced layouts, optimize power distribution, and manage noise isolation for sensitive analog sections.</li><li><strong>Placement &amp; Routing</strong>: Execute optimized placement and routing with a focus on timing, power, congestion, crosstalk, and integration with analog domains.</li><li><strong>Clock Tree Synthesis (CTS)</strong>: Design robust, low-power, low-EMC clock distribution networks that minimize coupling into analog circuits.</li><li><strong>Timing Closure (STA)</strong>: Act as STA expert, identifying and resolving complex timing issues across corners and mixed-signal interfaces.</li><li><strong>Verification &amp; Reliability</strong>: Perform EMIR (Electro-Migration &amp; IR Drop) checks and apply <strong>Design for Manufacturability (DFM)</strong> principles to enhance yield and robustness.</li><li><strong>Flow &amp; Automation</strong>: Improve physical design flows and develop automation scripts (Tcl, Python, Perl) to increase efficiency.</li><li><strong>Cross-functional Collaboration</strong>: Work closely with frontend, analog, CAD, and DFT teams to ensure seamless integration and accurate timing constraints.</li><li><strong>Technical Leadership</strong>: Provide guidance and support to peers, sharing best practices on mixed-signal integration, low-power, EMIR, and DFM.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>| WHAT DO WE EXPECT FROM YOU ?</strong></p><p><br></p><ul><li>Master’s or PhD in <strong>Microelectronics</strong>.</li><li><strong>7+ years of relevant experience</strong> in physical design for complex mixed-signal ICs.</li><li>Expert-level skills in <strong>STA</strong> and <strong>timing closure</strong>.</li><li>Proven experience with <strong>complex floorplans</strong> and sensitive analog interfaces.</li><li>Strong understanding of <strong>RTL (Verilog)</strong> for debugging and collaboration.</li><li>Advanced knowledge of <strong>Cadence EDA tools</strong> (Innovus, Genus, Tempus, Voltus, Comformal, Pegasus, Quantus).</li><li>Skilled in <strong>automation scripting</strong> (Tcl, Python, Perl).</li><li>Solid grasp of <strong>semiconductor manufacturing processes</strong> and digital design rules.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving, communication, and teamwork abilities.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>| WHAT IS EMPLOYENEURSHIP?</strong></p><p>Employeneurship is built around five key pillars:</p><ul><li><strong>Job security:</strong> Enjoy a permanent employment contract, ensuring stability and security.</li><li><strong>Full transparency:</strong> Know your financial value and benefit individually from a share of the profits generated.</li><li><strong>Personalized coaching:</strong> Receive individual coaching designed to develop your entrepreneurial skills.</li><li><strong>Competence cells:</strong> Access a strong, meaningful, and relevant professional network.</li><li><strong>Entrepreneurial lab:</strong> A playground for new ideas and a potential launchpad for startups.</li></ul><p><br></p><p>📢 <strong>Interested?</strong> Visit our TMC page: <u>www.themembercompany.com</u></p><p>Follow us on <strong>LinkedIn</strong> to stay updated on our latest news and opportunities! 🚀</p>",
