, or exclusive insights to day-one stories.</li><li>Curate a body of work that enhances ownership of industry subject matter or specialized expertise e.g. data journalism, interviews, technology, etc.</li><li>Collaborate with reporters, analysts, and subject-matter experts to create a cohesive product within the parameters given.</li><li>Develop and execute editorial news strategies alongside the Newsroom Manager and/or editorial line.</li><li>Manage the daily publishing schedule and ensure all deadlines are met.</li><li>Edit and fact-check articles for accuracy, clarity, and house style.</li><li>Develop and maintain a strong network of PR contacts, industry professionals, and community sources to support story development &amp; data acquisition.</li><li>Provide mentorship and constructive feedback to writers, supporting their professional development.</li><li>Assist in forward planning around major gambling industry news cycles including quarterly reporting, legislative cycles &amp; sports markets etc.</li><li>Act as the lead editor for a product or products, taking responsibility for performance and content quality.</li><li>Participate in cross-team collaborations to produce multimedia, business, or data-driven stories.</li><li>Uphold and model best practices in ethical journalism and online conduct. <br><br></li></ul><strong>Qualifications<br><br></strong><ul><li>Proven experience as an editor, section editor, or journalist in gambling or a closely related field.</li><li>Ability to motivate a fully remote team, and be leading by example.</li><li>Strong track record of writing and editing compelling, accurate, and timely content.</li><li>Deep understanding of the iGaming &amp; betting landscape, including major brands, people, events, organisations, and industry trends.</li><li>Ability to manage multiple projects, deadlines, and writers in a fast-paced newsroom environment.</li><li>Excellent editorial judgement and attention to detail.</li><li>Confident communicator with the ability to build key relationships with industry stakeholders.</li><li>Comfortable working with various CMS and SEO tools to align with brand strategy.</li><li>Strong grasp of journalistic ethics, fact-checking processes, and source development.</li><li>Ability to mentor junior writers.<br><br></li></ul><strong>Benefits &amp; Rewards<br><br></strong><ul><li>A brilliant opportunity to grow your career &amp; work with a fun, fast-paced &amp; growing company, prepared to let you shine</li><li>An entrepreneurial environment where you learn more every day (we more than welcome and support people with their own projects)</li><li>Build an organization that continues to diversify its portfolio</li><li>Personal responsibility with a ton of autonomy</li><li>33 free paid days</li><li>Market-leading remuneration and bonuses available</li><li>An international team with over 35 nationalities</li><li>Fully Remote working </li><li>Additional benefits for permanent employees are available depending on the location<br><br></li></ul><strong>What do we mean by \"Fully Remote\"<br><br></strong>Clickout Media offers you an unparalleled working experience. We are registered in Malta, but you don't have to be. Wherever you are based, and whether you are employed, operate B2B, or are a career freelancer, we will always find a way to work with great people.<br><br>Engaging with a worldwide workforce, ClickOut Media brings together world-leading experts in the fields of Tech, SEO, Content, and Product. Our remote approach gives absolute flexibility to our people and exemplifies our philosophy of autonomy and trust.<br><br>Diversity is a given to us, and this unique approach allows us to deliver and have respect for the wide variety of people, experiences, and cultures we bring together.<br><br><strong>Our Recruitment Process Is As Follows<br><br></strong><ul><li>Apply</li><li>Have an introduction call with our recruitment team</li><li>Do a test</li><li>Have a technical interview<b