g the maintenance, refresh, or retirement of services, systems, and technologies.</li><li>Consultation and Design Alignment: Consult on infrastructure and application projects to ensure alignment with the overall architecture and modify designs as needed.</li><li>Architectural Design and Guidance: Create architectural designs to support product, service, and system development, ensuring alignment with enterprise architecture and project execution plans.</li></ul><li>We offer a permanent contract based on hybrid working mode.<br><br></li></ul><strong>About You<br></strong><ul><li>Bachelor degree or equivalent experience in computer science, information-technology, engineering, system analysis or a related study.</li><li>Relevant work experience of minimum five years in at least five IT solution development disciplines, including technical and infrastructure architecture, network management, application development, middleware, database management or cloud development, with exposure to multiple, diverse technologies, platforms and processing environments.</li><li>Competencies:</li><ul><li>Knowledge on: </li><li>AWS Cloud (EC2, RDS, S3, VPC, R53, IAM…)</li><li>Azure Cloud</li><li>SAP RISE </li><li>On Premise Datacenter Architecture (On Premise Hardware : Data room rack / power, SAN Storage) </li><li>DevOps principles and Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery (CI/CD) pipelines</li><li>Active Directory / Entra ID / DNS; OS </li><li>Windows Server / Linux </li><li>Database : Microsoft SQL Server, Oracle, PostGre</li><li>Network protocols and technologies (TCP/IP, VLANS)</li><li>IT security (TLS, FW …)</li><li>ITIL service management processes </li><li>Technical and Management Expertise: Proficient in system development methodologies (e.g., agile, DevOps), ITSM, ITIL, and hybrid cloud architecture, with strong planning, analytical, and communication skills.</li><li>Strategic and Emerging Trends: Experienced in applying emerging technologies and supporting agile teams 